tweet: We can¬†and should¬†learn lessons from other communities‚Äîlisten to the science, be prepared, act swiftly, and save lives.

name: Governor Tony Evers
tweet: But the bad news is that it isn't enough--we need more. We need PPE and our requested lab supplies in order to increase our capacity to test tens of thousands of Wisconsinites, isolate those who are infected, and do our best to contain the spread of the disease.

name: Governor Tony Evers
tweet: The good news is that, due to the generosity of hundreds of Wisconsin businesses, non-profits, and even individuals, we‚Äôve been able to start distributing donated PPE into our local¬†communities.

name: Governor Tony Evers
tweet: Wisconsinites can now go to  https://covid19supplies.wi.gov/Donations¬† to either donate or sell large quantities of PPE to the state of Wisconsin, such as masks, gloves, and gowns.

name: Governor Tony Evers
tweet: So in addition to working with the federal government to get our share and working to make large purchases in partnership with our neighbors in the Midwest, last week we also launched a PPE Donation and Buyback program.

name: Governor Tony Evers
tweet: Wisconsin is competing not just with other states and the federal government but with the entire world to get these supplies‚Äîthis is a global crisis.

name: Governor Tony Evers
tweet: At the same time, we have continued to work at the state and regional level to purchase supplies and equipment, including PPE, testing supplies, and ventilators.

name: Governor Tony Evers
tweet: In addition to our SNS shipments, we have also requested PPE from FEMA which is critically necessary to protect our first responders and health care workers who are on the front lines of the COVID-19 battle.

name: Governor Tony Evers
tweet: As of today, we have received about half of these items and have been working this weekend to start distributing this PPE to local communities.
